File: A face mask lying on the ground. AFP/Roslan Rahman  JOHANNESBURG - Wearing masks indoors may soon be a thing of the past.     Health Minister Joe Phaahla has recommended the dropping of some key Covid-19 rules. These include the wearing of masks, limits on gatherings, and entry requirements. READ: COVID-19 in SA | Mask-wearing rule remains He has now asked his MECs to comment on the proposal. The memo sent to them says there has been a decline in cases, hospitalisations, and deaths. The recommendations will be presented to Cabinet on Wednesday.